<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Resolution:<P>I realized this morning that my measurements of angular diameter are not correlated directly to linear diameter as I had supposed. This should have struck me, but living in a heavily forest area I guess I never though about the horizon -- that is exactly what the angular diameter really is, the angle going underneath from one horizon to another, just from a great height. The difference between the corrected results using this and my previous, flawed method are small when examining very distant, small objects, but not in this case. The error is most evident when looking at Norrath from Luclin. I can probably correct the calculations on my own, but if anyone else wants to try it, then go ahead. Good luck!
</FONT>
<HR size="1" color="#a62a2a">
