<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
The simplest answer I could make is that someone has too much time on their hands... but I can contribute a few points.<P>There is no constant to measure the distance zone barriers represent.  In some zones one can "see" the other side.  In others (particularly ocean zones) there may be a greater distance involved.<P>Corresponding 1 loc to one foot seems to generate a VERY poor movement rate for characters.  Where did this number come from?  Why is it in imperial not metric?  Is the imperial measure fixed or, as with real world historical kingdoms, is it set based on the actual measurements of the current ruler?  In that case a foot in Oggok would be much larger than a foot in Ak'anon.<P>Certain areas shown on maps appear innacessible to PCs.  This includes moutain ranges, polar regions and certain forests.  How much land space do they occupy?<P>And, finally, is science the best system to use in a realm where magic is so prevalent?
</FONT>
