<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
That's quite a bit of impressive math.   <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0"><P>All I can say is this: the people who designed the zones and appearances of the original game did a very poor job of lining up zones and making them roughly the same size compared to each other.  What this means is that if you try and line up zones that *should* fit together, like the loop of Kithicor Forest, Rivervale, Misty Thicket, Runnyeye, Gorge of King Xorbb, East Karana, and Highpass Hold, they wind up being all out of whack.  They did a bit better with Kunark (although you can't fit Cabilis in there with LOIO no matter what you do), and better with Velious, but I think they're back to their original ways in Luclin.<P>The point is that, although you can base very complex measurements on what you find, I can almost guarantee you that Verant did not work through these calculations prior to developing any of the art or zones.  You are bound to be frustrated and have things not work out right because of that.  I think you're giving them way too much credit, and I wouldn't have even expected them to work this stuff out, since it would have no bearing on the final game, and would only restrict what they did instead of opening up new areas to explore.<P>--------------------<P>Muse<BR>Bard and Cartographer
</FONT>
