<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Exactly! I had tried lining up several of the newer zones together (thinking the mistakes of past zone alignment would have been fixed), specifically Paludal Caverns, Shar Vahl, Shadeweaver's Thicket and Hollowshade Moor... and guess what? Shar Vahl is about the third of the length it should be. ALSO, I judged the one foot equals one /loc measure on very rough guesswork; yes it is a poor estimation of character movement. I convinced myself it was reasonable looking at the spires, the bridge and the trees in North Karana with a high elf I was exploring with, but so many other experiences have undermined this assumption that I am not sure it is reasonable. It seems maybe intended, though: the developers are American, remember? The point about zone barriers is well taken. As a matter of fact, Velious and Antonica overlay the same space if zero movement is assumed over zone boundaries; then again teleporting because one steps over an line in the landscape is awfully unrealistic too. Since I used only Antonica to calculate the size of Norrath, and since Antonica is supposed to be seamless and 360 square miles in Online Adventures, the problem of unoccupied regions was "eliminated." But really, it is hard to explain them within the context of the original EverQuest: why should there be so many inaccessable plateaus and uncrossable mountains around the world? My method has been to use only the games themselves as canon material; many of the problems we encounter in the present analysis would probably dissolve if we looked instead at the associated literature and game fiction. Is it right to conduct a scientific analysis on a fictional world? Try the Star Wars Technical Commentaries (http://www.theforce.net/swtc), which is much, much more successful at explaining that universe than I am at this one. Ah... lastly the comment about to much time on my hands? That is sort of true now that my computer has trouble playing EverQuest, but still I can spend it pretty quickly doing other stuff and, at times, working on the things I am actually assigned. Anyway, I hope it was an interesting piece.<P>Reshokor Muiren,<BR>Dragon of the Outer Planes,<BR>Broodmate to Geshoren<P>Skorazu Hissanthi,<BR>Necromancer of the Thirty Fourth Scale,<BR>World of Torvonnilous
</FONT>
